of galaxies. The most cored galaxies are expected to have Vrot {$\sim$} 50 km s-1, with {$\alpha$} decreasing for more massive disc galaxies: spirals with Vrot {$\sim$} 150 km s-1 have central slopes {$\alpha$} {$\leq$} -0.8, approaching again the Navarro-Frenk-White profile. This novel prediction for the dependence of {$\alpha$} on disc galaxy mass can be tested using observational data sets and can be applied to theoretical modelling of mass profiles and populations of disc galaxies.},
