ngth of r\_e\_{\textasciitilde}0.43 kpc. While the data show the same excess with respect to the exponential law fits as found for the King model fits, this excess is not more severe than is seen in many disk systems. The current data, therefore, do not argue against the hypothesis that the halo dwarfs are the results of ram-pressure stripping of dI systems by the Galactic halo.},
