ion. Our GCE models with this yield normalization are consistent with most available observations, though the implied \$y{\textbackslash}mathrm\{\_\{He\}{\textasciicircum}\{CC\}\}\$ is low compared to most of the published massive star models. More precise measurements of \${\textbackslash}Delta Y\$ in stars and gas across a wide range of metallicity and [\${\textbackslash}alpha\$/Fe] ratio could test our models more stringently, either confirming the simple picture suggested by our calculations or revealing surprises in the evolution of the second most abundant element.},
